# Personal Codex Rules

This section applies to the home-level Codex environment.

## Superpowers Whitelist

Only the following superpowers skills are enabled by the recommended baseline:

- `brainstorming`
- `dispatching-parallel-agents`
- `finishing-a-development-branch`
- `receiving-code-review`
- `requesting-code-review`
- `subagent-driven-development`
- `systematic-debugging`
- `test-driven-development`
- `verification-before-completion`
- `writing-plans`
- `writing-skills`

Do not use any other skill from the installed `superpowers` library unless the user explicitly changes this whitelist.

## Superpowers Activation Policy

Keep superpowers as an available workflow library, not as a global mandatory startup routine.

- Do not load `using-superpowers` at session startup.
- Do not invoke a superpowers skill solely because a new conversation started or because the user sent a greeting.
- Invoke enabled superpowers only when the user explicitly names one or the current task matches the skill purpose.
- Treat `verification-before-completion` as the only always-on completion guard before claiming code work is done.
- Treat `systematic-debugging` as task-triggered for bugs, failing tests, errors, and unexpected behavior.
- Treat `receiving-code-review` as task-triggered when the user provides review feedback.
- Treat planning, TDD, review, subagent, branch-finishing, and skill-writing superpowers as task-triggered workflows.

